# IPC & TypeScript Services

## invoke() pattern — always this shape

```ts
import { invoke } from '@tauri-apps/api/core';

export async function commandName(param: ParamType): Promise<ReturnType> {
  return invoke<ReturnType>('command_name', { param });
}
```

- Typed generic on `invoke<T>` — never untyped.
- One exported function per Tauri command. No mega-service files.
- File name matches domain: `fileService.ts`, `settingsService.ts`.

## Composables (use\*.ts)

```ts
export function useFeature() {
  const data = ref<Type | null>(null)
  const error = ref<string | null>(null)
  const loading = ref(false)

  async function load() {
    loading.value = true
    error.value = null
    try {
      data.value = await commandName(...)
    } catch (e) {
      error.value = String(e)
    } finally {
      loading.value = false
    }
  }

  return { data, error, loading, load }
}
```

- Always expose `{ data, error, loading }` triad.
- Never swallow errors silently.

## Types

- Shared types (matching Rust structs) in `src/types/` as `.d.ts` files.
- Don't duplicate type definitions — import from `src/types/`.
- `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections.
- No `any`. If Tauri returns unknown shape, type it explicitly.

## Events (Tauri → frontend)

```ts
import { listen } from '@tauri-apps/api/event';

const unlisten = await listen<PayloadType>('event-name', (event) => {
  // handle event.payload
});
// cleanup: call unlisten() in onUnmounted
```

- Always store and call `unlisten()` on component unmount.
